A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, and I pretended to be working from home, but in reality, I was editing "Addicted."
If this damn file could just open. (OneDrive is truly crap.)
*The Hacker's Voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the sound was super loud. Awesome.
Turning the air purifier to the highest setting felt a bit too aggressive, but I did smell the wood shavings, so it's understandable. Plus, he's against wearing masks. And I do need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can't sleep until he leaves.
The good news is that Chapter 4 is finally edited!
Chapter Five is really long and super anxiety-inducing. Yeah! It's so exciting.
Searching and replacing... ➡️ ellipsis, there are 54 instances in this chapter 😅
But I still insist on this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally agitated.
The floor repairman is vacuuming, hoping that this means he is almost done.
He went out (it sounded like) cutting something. I peeked at the progress. There's still a lot of work to do :(
There are still 7 pages left in Chapter Five. It's still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in quite good shape—mainly needing some layout adjustments and minor tweaks to active voice and conciseness. But I really need to take a break and have a cup of tea, while that guy is still busy in my kitchen.
He's starting to use the vacuum cleaner again. Hopefully, this is a good omen.
The worker who was repairing the kitchen floor has left!
He told me that he quoted the price for repairing the entire floor, but the landlord was too cheap and only agreed to pay for fixing the part near the door that had already rotted. It feels much better now.
I'm drinking tea in the garden while the air purifier works hard in the kitchen, purifying the air in the room!
